    h3 Training Programs
    p A number of local bike shops host training rides to help riders get ready for the big ride!  This training group grows every year.  It is a very welcoming atmosphere with a positive vibe! It is a great way to meet friendly local cyclists who are committed to fighting HIV/AIDS. You will also get in shape!

    h3 Schedule
    p.text-danger 2016 training schedule TBD

    h3 Training Ride Details
    h4 When?
    p The training rides occur every Saturday morning until the event, starting in August.  Exact schedule TDB.

    h4 How Far?
    p The mileages each week increases for the 30, 65, and 100 mile routes. Training Ride Leaders will assist you on the road. No one is left behind!

    h4 Where to Meet?
    p Each ride will start and end at a local Santa Cruz area bike shop. They will OPEN EARLY for our training rides.  Some shops may offer special discounts.s

    h4 Ride Sponsors
    p We'll help you get fueled up for fun by offering some snacks in the morning.  Coffee will be provided courtesy of
      a(href='http://www.cafeugly.com/Cafeugly/home.html')  The Ugly Mug
      | .

    h4 Rider Conduct
    p Helmets ARE required!  Please bring two full water bottles, 2 energy bars, and tire patch kit.  Also, please eat breakfast before riding!  A road bike / hybrid is suggested for longer rides, but not required.

    p Stay connected and updated by joining the 
      a(href='https://www.facebook.com/groups/surfcityAIDSridetraining/') Facebook training group


